title: Arthur's Pass rocked by earthquakes overnight
text:
Arthur's Pass rocked by earthquakes overnight Last updated 05:27, February 24 2017 GEONET 
A magnitude 4.9 earthquake at Arthur's Pass at 2.35am was followed by a series of aftershocks. 
The Arthur's Pass area has been rocked by a flurry of earthquakes overnight. 
Did you feel the quakes? Send your newstips, photos and videos to 
The first was a magnitude 4.9 quake around 2.35pm, at a depth of 8km, 25km southeast of Arthur's Pass. 
GeoNet described it as severe, with 216 felt reports received by 5am - one of them severe, and three strong. 
It was followed by another half dozen quakes strong enough to be felt in the next few hours ranging in magnitude between 2.8 and 4.0.
